cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on the analysis of social activity data and the effect of social influence on product adoption and usage. 
2. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper investigates problems that have captured the attention of sociologists and proposes a model to simulate and analyze social behavior. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a probabilistic model and an inference method to fit the model parameters, which involves solving a convex program. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the adoption and usage of competing products, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed model and inference method, which involves solving a collection of smaller subproblems and scaling easily to networks with hundreds of thousands of nodes.
